# UI Component Guidelines

- This project uses various Radix UI primitives for accessible components
- Follow accessibility best practices:
  - Ensure proper ARIA attributes
  - Maintain keyboard navigation
  - Support screen readers
- When implementing Radix UI components:
  - Use the appropriate component for the interaction pattern
  - Customize styling using Tailwind classes
  - Follow the compound component pattern
- For form elements:
  - Use react-hook-form for form state management
  - Implement zod for form validation
  - Utilize Radix UI form primitives for accessible inputs
- For complex UI patterns:
  - Use react-resizable-panels for resizable layouts
  - Implement embla-carousel-react for carousels
  - Use sonner for toast notifications
  - Leverage vaul for drawer components
- When creating new UI components:
  - Ensure they are responsive
  - Test across different viewports
  - Maintain consistency with existing components
